f=AI & Agents/proto/custom/promote-or-archive-verdict/SKILL.md · in=hard stop prototype's expiry: score against frozen criteria, exactly one PROMOTE (into Rail new-agent path) ARCHIVE (with learnings captured). Silence archive. Default-promote forbidden (Fleet Charter Rail 4). · p=Prototypes linger become shadow agents unaudited, half-caged, load-bearing accident. mandatory verdict keeps cage meaningful turns even failures recorded learnings. · wu=prototype's expiry date arrives (calendar-driven, memory-driven registry's expiry field trigger)., operator/agent asks early verdict (allowed; early archive always available, early promote still needs full criteria). · st:/ Protocol=SCORE (eval-first-design's frozen criteria, mechanical possible) VERDICT (all criteria pass PROMOTE eligible; any fail ARCHIVE, documented operator override promote-with-known-gaps visible, signed) PROMOTE: PROPOSAL (Rail new-agent proposal meta: full house structure agent-architecture-standards, migration prototype shape itemized) ARCHIVE: LEARNINGS (what hypothesis taught, verbatim evidence anneal's lessons ledger; prototype's artifacts archived read-only) REGISTRY (meta: state change either way). · in=verdict against FROZEN criteria mid-flight impressions, sunk cost, "so close" inadmissible. (This discipline skill; rationalization table below exists because pressure guaranteed.) PROMOTE produces proposal, agent: board/operator gate like any fleet change; prototype stays caged until proposal lands. ARCHIVE success mode: learnings entry mandatory specific (which criterion failed, why, what change answer). archive without learnings wasted experiment. Expiry verdict logged auto-archive, flagged gauge's health report missed verdict process failure worth seeing). Re-prototyping archived hypothesis requires delta stated against learnings entry (scout's re-open discipline, borrowed). · in=\| Rationalization \| Reality \| · in=\|---\|---\| · in=\| "It just needs another week" \| Extension is a Rail 3 proposal, once. Otherwise: verdict now. \| · in=\| "It's basically passing" \| Any fail = archive or a SIGNED operator override. "Basically" is a fail. \| · in=\| "We already use it for real work" \| That's a shadow agent — worse than archiving. Verdict now, incident if load-bearing. \| · in=\| "Archiving wastes the work" \| The learnings entry IS the work. Lingering wastes it. \| · of=Verdict record: scored table, PROMOTE/ARCHIVE, proposal ref learnings-ledger ref, registry state change. · pr=prototype ends date, purpose, writing., Archive success; shadow agents failure., Overrides exist visible signed, never implied. · f=Criteria couldn't scored (measurement infrastructure failed mid-trial)? Verdict ARCHIVE `unscoreable infrastructure` learnings, re-prototype delta "fix measurement" never promote unscored criteria. · b:with Other Skills=Consumes eval-first-design's frozen criteria; ends agent-prototype-kit's cage., PROMOTE path: meta (architecture standards registry governance). ARCHIVE path: anneal (lessons ledger)., gauge surfaces missed verdicts.